{'verification': 'Models are verified by comparing predicted temperature trajectories with experimental data during calibration.', 'validation': 'Assumptions (uniform temperature distribution, negligible heat loss to walls) are validated through experiments (e.g., uniformity tests with fans at 12V and 18V).', 'uncertainties': 'Parameters like G_box and G_heater are calibrated to minimize residual errors (using SciPy\u2019s least-squares optimization).', 'errors': 'Temperature sensors have \u00b10.5\u00b0C accuracy (validated for -10\u00b0C to +85\u00b0C). Model accuracy depends on calibration success and assumption validity.'}